--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components and their provenance
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project builds on, adapts, or interoperates with the following works.
Their original licenses apply to the corresponding code and continue to govern
the portions derived from them.

* CLAM — Clustering-constrained Attention Multiple-instance Learning
  Mahmood Lab. License: GPL-3.0.
  https://github.com/mahmoodlab/CLAM
  The attention-MIL backbone (CLAM_SB / CLAM_MB), the whole-slide-image
  utilities (`visualization/wsi_core`, `visualization/vis_utils`), and the
  heatmap/preset machinery are derived from CLAM. Pheno-MYCN is distributed
  under GPL-3.0 in compliance with this lineage.

* TransMIL — Transformer-based Correlated MIL
  Shao et al., NeurIPS 2021.
  https://github.com/szc19990412/TransMIL
  Used as a baseline classifier (`pheno_mycn/models/TransMIL.py`).

* DSMIL / dual-stream MIL (MILNet)
  Li et al., CVPR 2021.
  https://github.com/binli123/dsmil-wsi
  Used as a baseline classifier (`pheno_mycn/models/MILNet.py`).

* timm — PyTorch Image Models (optimizer factory: RAdam, Lookahead)
  Ross Wightman. License: Apache-2.0.
  https://github.com/huggingface/pytorch-image-models
  The optimizer factory in `pheno_mycn/optimizers/` is adapted from timm.

* nystrom-attention
  Phil Wang (lucidrains). License: MIT.
  https://github.com/lucidrains/nystrom-attention
  Required by the TransMIL baseline.

* UNI — universal histopathology tile encoder
  Mahmood Lab.
  https://github.com/mahmoodlab/UNI
  Used upstream to produce the 1024-d tile embeddings consumed by Pheno-MYCN.

* HoverNet — nuclear segmentation/classification
  vqdang. License: MIT.
  https://github.com/vqdang/hover_net
  Used upstream to produce the cell-level maps consumed by the cell-level
  statistics and latent-space experiments.

Each upstream project remains the property of its respective authors. Where this
repository redistributes adapted source, the original copyright notices are
retained in the relevant files.
